{
  "texts": [
    "We set the temperature to 1.0 because the GPT-5 models do not allow variation from this value.",
    "Furthermore, a temperature of 1.0 is consistent with previous work [28], and even when variation is allowed, temperatures of 0.0 are not always deterministic with OpenAI models [6].",
    "To control API costs, especially for the larger models, we evaluated all models on the same set of 50 puzzles, consistent with prior work [28].",
    "Prompting StrategiesWe study three prompting regimes under a common setup: Zero-Shot (no examples or reasoning cues), CoT (three worked examples encouraging stepwise reasoning), and AoT (three examples implementing a simple Manhattan-style search).",
    "The CoT and AoT prompts use the same three example boards, differing only in the reasoning styles they demonstrate."
  ]
}